<item>
            <title>[OAK-795] Osgi init issues</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-795</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently there are some init issues when running in an OSGi env - there can be more than one call to Oak#createContentRepository using the same NodeStore.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The overlap can come from having a Sling repo call #createContentRepository via the JCR class and at the same time have  &lt;em&gt;org.apache.jackrabbit.mk.osgi.MicroKernelService&lt;/em&gt; call #createContentRepository on the same NodeStore from the Activator.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The simplest solution for now is to have the oak-core Activator class ignore the NodeStore services and leave repo impls like the sling one call #createContentRepository.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
